Many of you are asking about implementing 
anti-aging steps/products into your skincare regimen. In NC line, besides using C’me Vitamin C Serum and Splash Hyaluronic Acid Serum we love Resurfacing Glycolic Toner 🥰
How to RGT:
Use after cleansing 3xweek in PMs
Spritz on cotton pad wipe face and neck
Follow with your fave face mist, serums, face oil

❣️❣️❣️
SPF daily moisturizer in AMs is mandatory! Especially on days when you are using Resurfacing Glycolic Toner. While you are stripping damaged layers of the skin and stimulating production of collagen, you are at the same time weakening protective barrier of the skin. Use only 3xweek on regular base and use SPF in the morning ❣️❣️❣️

🔟 Reasons why Sheet Masks are endangering our environment 👇

1️⃣ Single-Use Plastics: Sheet face masks often come individually packaged in single-use plastic, contributing to the global plastic pollution crisis.
2️⃣ Non-Biodegradable Materials: Many sheet masks are made from non-biodegradable materials, leading to long-term environmental harm as they do not break down easily.
3️⃣ Chemical Contaminants: The production and disposal of sheet masks can release harmful chemicals into the environment, affecting ecosystems and wildlife.
4️⃣ Excessive Packaging: In addition to the masks themselves, the excessive packaging used for branding and marketing purposes contributes to unnecessary waste.
5️⃣ Energy Consumption: The manufacturing process of sheet masks consumes significant energy, contributing to carbon emissions and environmental degradation.
6️⃣ Water Usage: The production of sheet masks often requires substantial water resources, potentially impacting water-stressed regions.
7️⃣ Transportation Emissions: Sheet masks are frequently manufactured in one location and shipped globally, leading to carbon emissions from transportation.
8️⃣ Microplastic Pollution: Some sheet masks contain microplastics, which can enter water systems and pose threats to aquatic life and human health.
9️⃣ Lack of Recycling Options: Due to the mixed materials used in sheet masks and their packaging, recycling options are limited, resulting in more waste ending up in landfills.
🔟 Consumer Behavior Impact: The convenience of single-use sheet masks may contribute to a disposable mindset among consumers, further exacerbating environmental issues.

Nature’s Kitchen 👩‍🍳 
This yummy DIY face mask is perfect for dry seasons. It’s easy, loaded with vitamins, minerals and nutrients. Literally food for skin and that’s the way we like it 😋

All you need:
1 banana
1 egg yolk 
2tsp olive oil
2tsp flour 

I like to use this face mask while resting, laying down and doing my breathing exercises. I also like to use piece of cheese cloth over it. It prevents it from dripping.

Store leftovers in refrigerator covered with foil. Lasts up to four days and can be used daily.

Remember 🦉 
Achieving and maintaining healthy skin comes down to healthy skincare routine so your Am/Pm skincare regimen is must have in place 💪
